This line is likely causing the issue for you, due to the fact that whatever is in `cellData` is not being successfully converted to a `double`:

    Double dDate = Convert.ToDouble(cellData);

Instead of `Convert.ToDouble`, try instead to use `double.TryParse`:

    if (double.TryParse(cellData, out double dDate))
    {
        ... The rest of your code
    }
    else
    {
        // cellData is NOT a double. Do something here to handle it
    }

The reason to change this is because `TryParse` returns a boolean indicating whether it has been successful or not **rather than throwing an exception**.

This gives you a graceful way to handle the conversion failure.

